## Quick Start

```bash
# Clone and install
git clone https://github.com/hferrándiz/retail-demand-intelligence.git
cd retail-demand-intelligence
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run pipeline
make ingest        # Download M5 + weather (requires Kaggle API key)
make transform     # Bronze -> Silver
make classify      # ADI/CV2 + ABC/XYZ classification
make train_lgbm    # LightGBM global + quantile
make evaluate      # 5-fold rolling-origin backtesting
make generate_inventory  # Monte Carlo simulation
make export_serving      # JSON serving assets

# Run dashboard locally
cd app && npm install && npm run dev
# -> http://localhost:5173

# Run all tests
pytest tests/ -q   # 795 tests
make lint          # ruff + mypy
```

**Prerequisites:**
- `KAGGLE_USERNAME` and `KAGGLE_KEY` env vars (for M5 download)
- `FRED_API_KEY` env var (optional, for macro features)
- Node.js 20+ (for frontend)

See [docs/09_deployment_guide.md](docs/09_deployment_guide.md) for full setup instructions.

